 Pavel Kudryavtsev 123RF.comThe building material retailer typically serves home builders and improvers, contractors and traders. Revenue was up 15% to R5.17bn, with the recently acquired P&L Hardware accounting for the big chunk (11%) of the revenue growth while 20 new stores accounted for the balance. "This increase [in revenue] for the period has been achieved in tough trading conditions with selling price inflation of 3%," the company said in a statement. The small-cap company declared an interim dividend of R5.40 per share, which was up 5% on the year-earlier period. The stock was up 0.61% to R369.25 in midmorning trade, valuing the company at R9.22bn. Source: BDpro